OL,3,CInside Southern Water's 'super sewer'
OL,4,Ckeeping the sea off Brighton safe
OL,6,FThese sewers date back to the 1870s,
OL,7,Fbuilt by hand in an incredible feat of
OL,8,Fengineering.
OL,10,FStill in use, despite their age, they
OL,11,Fbecame a blueprint for many that
OL,12,Ffollowed - raw sewage flowing through
OL,13,Fthem and then pumped into the sea.
OL,15,FThat didn't change until the 1990s.
OL,17,F"This overflow sewer is still
OL,18,Fperforming its job to this day," Simon
OL,19,FJudd of Southern Water said.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/18
