OL,3,CInside Southern Water's 'super sewer'
OL,4,Ckeeping the sea off Brighton safe
OL,6,F"With every heavy rainfall it would
OL,7,Foverflow and then come out through
OL,8,Foutfalls onto the beach.
OL,10,F"Years later, Southern Water realised
OL,11,Fthat's unacceptable and something had
OL,12,Fto be done. That's when we constructed
OL,13,Fa storm tunnel under Brighton beach."
OL,15,FThe result was a 'mini-super sewer'
OL,16,Fconstructed below Brighton and Hove in
OL,17,Fthe 2000s - fully operational since
OL,18,F2012.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/18
